    "collapsible_content_pMQR6F": {
      "type": "collapsible-content",
      "blocks": {
        "collapsible_tab_NcQwfi": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "1.How do I choose between a Cordless Vacuum and a Robotic Vacuum?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<ul><li>Choose a cordless vacuum if you need deep cleaning and versatility. It's perfect for cleaning high places, narrow corners, and car interiors, and it generally has stronger suction.Choose a robotic vacuum<\/li><li>if you need daily, automatic maintenance. It can keep your home consistently clean on a schedule, freeing you from manual chores.<br\/><\/li><\/ul>",
            "page": "",
            "custom_liquid": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_rK6KQR": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "2. How strong is the suction of your cordless vacuums? Can they clean carpets thoroughly?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>Our cordless vacuums have powerful suction. Most models feature a max power mode that effectively removes dust, pet hair, and debris from deep within carpets. Some models also come with specialized brush heads designed specifically for carpets, providing even better results.<\/p>",
            "page": "",
            "custom_liquid": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_LPUEyF": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "3. Are robotic vacuums suitable for homes with pets or children?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>Yes, they are a great choice. Robotic vacuums can easily pick up pet hair and everyday messes like food crumbs. Some of our models include anti-tangle technology and smart obstacle avoidance, which help them navigate around cords and toys without getting stuck.<\/p>",
            "page": "",
            "custom_liquid": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_hNVmh7": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "4. How do the robotic vacuums navigate and plan their cleaning path?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>Our robotic vacuums use Lidar laser navigation or vision-based navigation systems to accurately map your home and plan the most efficient cleaning route. You can set up no-go zones or specify particular areas for a deep clean.<\/p>",
            "page": "",
            "custom_liquid": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_wNkCyH": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "5. What is the battery life of these products?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>Battery life varies by model and usage mode. Generally, cordless vacuums run for 30-60 minutes on a standard setting, while robotic vacuums can clean for 90-180 minutes. Most models automatically return to their charging dock when the battery is low.<\/p>",
            "page": "",
            "custom_liquid": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_RXyHVW": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "6. Are they complicated to clean and maintain?",
            "open": false,
            "content": "<p>No, they are very easy to maintain. Most models feature a removable dustbin and washable filters for simple, regular cleaning. All our products include a detailed user manual, and you can also find tutorial videos on our website.<\/p>",
            "page": "",
            "custom_liquid": ""
          }
        }
